{
  "stem": "18581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a hell of a difference.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because Vilna was a old, established Jewish center with hundreds of synagogues.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In one place in the shul [NON-ENGLISH], they had more than 10 synagogues.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "While in my hometown, there was only one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a new town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it had only one synagogue, and before it, a little [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the good part was that there was a very intensive life around the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As an example, every day, the [HEBREW]-- that means the-- the group that studied Talmud-- that included my late father and myself-- used to meet, especially in the summer, around 6pm, for one hour, to study Talmud, together with the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the rabbi was [INAUDIBLE] Zeev Mamyoffe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Would you spell that, please.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Zeev.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Z-E-E-V.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Mamyoffe.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "M-A-M-Y-O-double-F-E.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And there were about 60, 70 participants.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Considering that the whole town had about two-- 200 Jewish families, it was a very high percentage of Jews educated in Talmud, who could participate in the [HEBREW], in the daily portion of the Talmud.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And from this point of view, it was probably one of the better organized towns-- small towns in-- in-- in Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And Jewish life, of course, centered around the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I attended in the shul [NON-ENGLISH] And I once I had the privilege of davening [HEBREW] with the Vilna [INAUDIBLE], Haim Ozer Grodzenski.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Haim Ozer Grodzenski.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "H-A-I-M O-Z-E-R G-R-O-D-Z-E-N-S-K-I.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Grodzenski.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Before he passed away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Reb ?] Haim Ozer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Vilna [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not the old Vilna [INAUDIBLE] that was 200 years ago, but the present [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was-- in-- in my hometown, they were not all religiously oriented.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But-- and those that were were mostly modern.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You didn't have any ultra-Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You didn't have any Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
